Problem: Majority Element II
Topic: Arrays, HashMap
Difficulty: Medium

Approach:
Use a hash map to count the frequency of each element in the array. After counting, traverse the map and add all elements whose frequency is greater than ⌊n/3⌋ to the result vector.

Time Complexity: O(n)
Space Complexity: O(n)

Code:

class Solution {
public:
    vector<int> majorityElement(vector<int>& nums) {
        unordered_map<int,int> mp;
        int n=nums.size();
        vector<int> final_arr;

        for(int x:nums){
            mp[x]++;
        }

        for(auto it:mp){
            if(it.second>n/3){
                final_arr.push_back(it.first);
            }
        }

        return final_arr;
    }
};
